To install healpy:


======== New install instruction >= 0.9.0 ==============

- get healpy:

svn co https://svn.lal.in2p3.fr/users/rosset/healpy/trunk healpy-trunk

or, for a tagged version (recommended)

svn co https://svn.lal.in2p3.fr/users/rosset/healpy/tags/healpy-0.9.0 healpy-0.9.0

- install it

cd healpy-trunk && python setup.py install

If you don't want to install it in the system directory (or don't have 
the rights to write there), you can build it and then copy the 
build/lib.xxx/healpy directory where you want. You will need to have the 
parent dirctory in sys.path.

Then, test it with :
import healpy as H
import numpy
H.mollview(numpy.arange(12))

======== Instruction for version < 0.9.0  ==============

- first you must get hpdata and hpbeta (just beside healpy in svn tree)

svn co https://svn.lal.in2p3.fr/users/rosset/healpy/tags/healpy-0.8.3 healpy-0.8.3
svn co https://svn.lal.in2p3.fr/users/rosset/hpdata hpdata
svn co https://svn.lal.in2p3.fr/users/rosset/hpbeta hpbeta

- Then, compile hpbeta

cd hpbeta
export HEALPIX_TARGET=generic_gcc
gmake

- then, compile healpy:

cd ../healpy-0.8.2
export HEALPIX_DATA=../hpdata
export HEALPIX_CXX=../hpbeta/generic_gcc
python setup.py build

- install healpy

python setup.py install [--prefix=/a/path/to/local]

(use the prefix option if you dont have the rights to write in standard python
package place)

- if you haven't put healpy in a standard place, don't forget to update your
  PYTHONPATH environment variable

Now you should be able to use healply

import healpy as H
m=arange(12)
H.mollview(m)
